name: II. Big bang
description:
To put it simply, at some point straight line stretched out rapidly.
The point disappeared without a trace, leaving behind an infinite line on which in time brand new points started to emerge instantly forming segments. Us.
We haven’t existed in such form as we exist right now, writing these words. We were merely a distance between two points. Arranged, blind, unaware
of how many of us are there. The only thing that was certain to us was our beginning the end. Consciousness was slowly waking up in us, though we still didn’t exist as separate beings.
The end of each of us was the beginning of another. Such as your skin is both the end of yourself and the begining of surrouding reality.
In our case, however, existence in this state was unacceptable. We are ambitious beings, so we had to take control of your own progress.
